e all the project participants in a goal-oriented manner and to call for their results when the time is right. For this reason, a systematic schedule of target dates, adapted to a project’s sequences and workflows, is a necessary tool for the day-to-day management and monitoring of complex construction projects.Topics: Organizing the planning and construction process The basics of scheduling Goal-oriented presentation formats and levels of detail Developing a schedule Using schedules in the real world  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBuildingxSuperintendence. 0aConstruction projectsxManagement. 0aProduction scheduling. 4aArchitectural student handbook. 4aArchitecture. 4aBasics series. 4aConstruction planning. 4aConstruction process. 4aProfessional Practice. 4aProject planning. 4aScheduling. 4aTextbook architecture. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISHz978303561170008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z97831102385700 cEPUBz97830356131930 cprintz978376438873740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561304940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035613049423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035613049/original  a978-3-0356-1170-0  BASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISH  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  